Glad to hear you liked it! Yes, nicely observed. The game was slower, but more physical. Seeler and Pelé are two entirely different types of players and both of absolute greatness, but Pelé is the more complete player, obviously with more flair, as you'd expect of a Brazilian. Seeler is the more powerful player physically (and he has better technique and passes than one would expect), but Pelé is almost as powerful, more elegant, and he has supreme technique

Fun fact: Seeler and Pelé were good friends, they remained pretty close for a long time. There are quite a few pics of them laughing together. Seeler died this July, aged 85.
Also, both Seeler and Pelé played four world cups: 1958, 1962, 1966, 1970. Pelé and Brazil won 58, 62, and 70, Seeler however was denied this great honor despite always coming close (58 semifinal, 66 final with the legendary Wembley goal, 70 semifinal). Seeler led Germany as the captain. He and Pelé had a race against each other: Who would be the first player to score in four different World Cups? In the end, Seeler edged Pelé out by three minutes.

I've habitually hidden myself away on 4chan since 2007 because I have zero social skills and am a total loser.

Major anxiety and depression due to having been criticized and judged my whole life. No matter what I say or do, I have seemingly never been good enough for anyone.

But I enjoy sports. Mainly watching sports nowadays, anyway. I used to recreationally play some sports when I was much younger, like street hockey and backyard/ lawn football (I never played any sports academically). Not anymore though. My motivation and energy levels are (and have been) nearly dead for years.

Nowadays, if I'm not wasting my life away here or watching the games or the latest highlights of NHL/NFL games, I'm usually writing. Journaling. It's my alternate way of coping with life. Watching sports and online sports related discussion have sort of become a mask for years of repressed pain. Journaling helps me cope with, come to terms with, and, to a certain extent, accept that pain for what it is.

Tl;dr
Perpetual loneliness sucks and I use sports as a mask much of the time to hide the pain of being lonely all the time. Maybe some of you can relate to what I've been dealing with for over 15 years of my life. I'll be turning 30 soon, not that it really matters anymore.

Now go ahead and call me a faggot for being honest and vulnerable with my feelings.

OP is always a faggot anyway.
